title.narrative: Governance Integration for Stabilization and Resilience (GISR)

description.narrative: (USAID Middle East Regional (MER)): The primary objective of GISR MENA is to sustainably strengthen local and national systems to adapt to shocks and stressors in the MENA region. GISR MENA supports U.S. foreign policy objectives by promoting stable, democratic governance in the region through expanding USAID's knowledge base and tools by advancing analysis of governance, resilience, and stabilization needs. GISR also initiates work to lay the foundation for longer-term, comprehensive programming to confront issues such as accountable and inclusive governance, participatory planning, essential service delivery, human rights, gender based violence prevention and response, addressing risk factors for instability/violent extremism, and strengthening community resilience. Programming, analysis, and training will include democracy and governance components and approaches such as engaging youth, civil society & media, and formal/informal institutions to address instability. Programming may support analysis and bridge activities involving engagement of women in governance and stabilization. Activities will support countries struggling to move along the development path toward sustainable political, economic, and social stability. This is a centrally managed mechanism into which Missions can invest their bilateral funds. A portion of this funding will contribute towards the DRG, GBV, and Combatting Child Marriage earmarks.
